Fatherhood took on a whole new meaning one year ago today. When I rushed my first born child “Trace” to the urgent care and then ended up in an ambulance as he was going into complete respiratory failure, the entire world stopped. After 6 days in the ICU My little man was finally released on Xmas eve. The only thing that kept us all together was our faith in the lord, and the whole “All I want for Christmas “ saying turned into a new meaning for our family for the rest of our lives. Cherish every moment you have with loved ones because at the end of everyday that is what matters the most. While my wife @apick_of_our_lives would love to forget what happened last year, shortly after Cate was born, we will strive together as a family as we bring one more baby girl into this world in April. I pray every night for many things, but mostly that anyone going through a similar experience will keep the faith. #blessed #faith #believer

Proud Dad moment last night. It must have been 40 years ago when I was sitting in that chair with my Dad. Trace was so scared walking into the blind at sunset but after we got settled in, he was absolutely perfect. 

I don’t know how long I had looked forward to this day but it was certainly before he was born. He learned the true meaning of hunting as we sat in the blind until almost 9pm and didn’t fire a shot. So blessed to have such a brave and well behaved boy(when it comes to hunting). He learned a very important lesson- and that’s to always listen to your Dad. I can’t wait for the seasons to come and of course the day we bag the trophy! @apick_of_our_lives @dwpick719

Earlier this week, I had the pleasure of catering a lunch for @truenorth_retreats 
As I was about to slice into the brisket, the blessing started, and I stopped, bowed my head, and prayed. Admittedly I prayed the brisket was cooked perfectly, but most importantly thanked God for allowing me to be a part of something very special. 

That day I learned more about True North and instantly felt a connection to their purpose and a strong desire to attend one of their upcoming retreats. 

From the Founder @nathanielwblackburn - “True North Retreats is a place for men to step away from the distractions of the world to spend quality time with the Father through solitude, adventure, and fellowship. We Unplug With Purpose to allow God to realign our spirits to our true identities as His sons.”

Most of us live hectic lives, and the idea of unplugging and allowing myself to come closer to God sounded like a dream vacation! 

For my “birthday fundraiser “ this year, I have chosen True North Retreats, and while donations would be incredible, spreading the word about this ministry would be even more appreciated. 

For more information see the link below or follow @truenorth_retreats 

https://www.truenorthretreats.org/mission
